title: For Sale:  Don't be dumb.
postcontent: Some of the prices listed here are ridiculous. You use the internet to make a posting, take 2 mins to search the firearm you are selling. I can't count how many people have their used firearms listed for the same price or even higher than msrp. (Some off roster being the exception...Not your 380 taurus) Then they wonder why no one wants to buy it and continually post it over and over.Sites like slickguns.com will give you the prices that many of the major gun stores and online gun stores charge all in one simple search. You get a list of them all and the price they charge. It also listing shipping charges if someone wants to order online. You can even feel free to add $30 for ffl transfer(what most local shops charge) to that price. Maybe you overpaid because you didn't do any research and bought a firearms from the most expensive place in town, just don't expect hardly anyone to overpay because you got taken by an overpriced store.$450 pistol brand new....and you want $550? 1911's for 2-400 over new dealer prices. Firearms hold their value well, but a used firearm is not worth the same amount or more than it costs brand new(antique, SOME off-roster and rare firearms excluded).Maybe you'll get lucky and find some dumb schmuck who has never used the search bar of the internet or walked into a gun store before making a purchase, but chances are you will be laughed at, mocked, and will not make a sale.Don't be dumb... delete your postings if you fall into the above catagory.
